results.question: How do I print in the library?
results.answer:
Here’s how to print in the libraries at Miami University (source: lib.miamioh.edu/libraryhealthy/tech/):

• Get your document into the MUprint queue  
  – From any campus computer or device, select “MUprint Black and White” or “MUprint Color” as your printer  
  – Email your PDF/image to MUprint-BW@MiamiOH.edu (black & white) or MUprint-Color@MiamiOH.edu  
  – Upload your PDF/image at MUprint.MiamiOH.edu  

• Release your job at the printer  
  – Scan the QR code on the printer with your phone, log in on the webpage, and tap to release (no touch required)  
  – Or swipe your Miami ID at the printer’s card reader and use the touchscreen to select and print your job  

• Printing costs per side remain:  
  – Black & White: 8.5” × 11” = 10¢ | 11” × 17” = 20¢  
  – Color: 8.5” × 11” = 25¢ | 11” × 17” = 50¢  

If you have any trouble, please drop by a service desk or call (513) 529-4141.

results.question: Can I check out a laptop?
results.answer:
Yes—you can borrow laptops from Miami University Libraries. Here’s how it works:

• **What’s available**  
  – **Chromebook laptops** (30-day checkout)  
  – **iPad Pros & Apple Pencils** (available at the Art & Architecture Library)  

• **How to borrow**  
  – Bring your Miami University ID to any library checkout desk (King, Wertz Art & Architecture, or other campus libraries)  
  – Log into the device on campus with your U-Number and password  

• **Loan periods & fees**  
  – Chromebooks: 30 days  
  – Damaged or lost laptops/tablets: up to \$2,000 replacement charge  

• **Check availability**  
  – Equipment availability can change quickly, so feel free to call ahead at **(513) 529-4141** before you come  

Source: https://www.lib.miamioh.edu/use/technology/tech-checkout/

results.question: How do I get Adobe?
results.answer:
You can check out an **Adobe Creative Cloud** license through Miami University Libraries just like you would reserve a study room—then download and install the apps on your own computer. Here’s how it works:

• Go to https://www.lib.miamioh.edu/software/  
• Under **Adobe Creative Cloud (Student)** select your checkout (14-day loan; Windows, macOS or iOS)  
• Log in with your Miami credentials, reserve the license, then follow the download/install instructions on that page  

If you only need to use Adobe while on campus, many library computers already have Creative Cloud installed—you’ll just “check out” a license at the info desk. For remote access, you can also connect to one of our lab machines via RemoteLab.MiamiOH.edu (over VPN) which has Creative Cloud ready to go.  

Questions? Call (513) 529-4141 or use our live chat at https://www.lib.miamioh.edu/research/research-support/ask/.
